          p
            | I hail from Espoo, neighboring Helsinki, the capital of Finland. I have a background in academics (English language and linguistics), in IT, in digital marketing, and in web development. I&rsquo;ve been programming actively since 1997, and I built my first website the same year. Marketing, IT disciplines, and web analytics all fell into my sphere of interest shortly after.
          p
            | My blog has a singular purpose: To tell complicated stories in a simple, understandable, and actionable way.
          p
            | Most often, I talk about 
            a(href='https://www.simoahava.com/categories/analytics/') web analytics
            | , but I also have soft spots for 
            a(href='https://www.simoahava.com/categories/digital-marketing/') digital marketing
            |  in general, for 
            a(href='https://www.simoahava.com/categories/seo/') SEO
            | , for 
            a(href='https://www.simoahava.com/categories/web-development/') web development
            | , and for 
            a(href='https://www.simoahava.com/tags/google-cloud/') working with the Google Cloud Platform
            | .
          p
            | I believe in the power of data and technology. I&rsquo;m also a strong advocate for altruistic knowledge sharing. You won&rsquo;t find a mailing list on this site (there&rsquo;s an 
            a(href='https://www.simoahava.com/index.xml') RSS feed for you
            | ), nor will you find me trying to peddle my wares or trying to push a commercial agenda. This blog is for transferring knowledge between me, my guest writers, and the community participating in the article comments (thank you!).
          p But enough about me. What about you? You&rsquo;ve come to the right place if you&rsquo;re:
